Can't you guys take this somewhere else? This "discussion" is turning into
a contest of wills.

To the TAMU INSTALL users:

  YOU ARE NOT GOING TO WIN. GIVE IT UP.

  You can not dictate to some one else what they must or must not do. If you
don't like XFree86 in the manner that it is offered, then get the X11R5
sources, and make your own package. Then, you may do your own server
implementation and have it do your own auto-configuration.

  You have made your REQUEST to the XFree86 group. Unfortuntely, it was not
accepted. It is very doubtfull that it will ever be accepted by the current
set of developers. Accept it as fact of life.

To the XFree86 people:

  Please do not judge all users of your package by a vocal few. Recognize
that every group of users (for any piece of software/hardware, whatever) has
a few who believe that their way is THE ONLY way.

  However, recognize that people will use the script. It is not in your
ability to prevent them from doing so. You have stated the reasons why it is
not a good idea. That is as far as you can go. Please let it drop there.
